caption: b'The IMTS Spark demo featuring the PUMA TT1300SYY kicks off at 11:00 AM (CST) today. It\xe2\x80\x99s the horizontal turning center with a range of capabilities that have to be seen to be believed. Don\xe2\x80\x99t miss it. Visit the link in our bio and save it to your MySpark Planner.'

b'A Doosan DNM 4500 being installed for a new customer. We know you have a choice when it comes to selecting machine tools and we thank you for flying (um, buying) Doosan. Repost @zandercncsolutions. "Ready to prove out the new programs on the 4th axis."'
b'The 5-axis DVF 6500 offers single-setup efficiency, a high speed spindle and, apparently, time travel capability. Happy Thanksgiving, everybody.'

b'For 15 years, Accelerated Tooling has been machining a variety of materials, and they trust their army of Doosan machines to help them continue to grow and succeed. Link in bio with full video. \n\n#DoosanShop #MachineGreatness'
b'Turned funnel parts made from 304L stainless steel coming from the machine shop. Repost @zerspanungstechnik.berlin. "Beautiful work."'

b'We could simply tell you how much everyone at @joegibbsracing loves the Doosan machines they work with, but we\xe2\x80\x99d rather you heard it straight from the horse\xe2\x80\x99s mouth. Link in bio for full video.'

b'Winner winner, turkey dinner! We have an October #PARTPRIDE champ, and it\xe2\x80\x99s @themachineiest from Orlando. His rear camera spring adapter made with the MX 2100ST netted him the prize box. If you want to enter, there\xe2\x80\x99s still time! Just share the pic or video of what your Doosan made with the #PARTPRIDE hashtag. Link in bio for his full story.'

b'Our next IMTS Spark demo is scheduled for December 1. Join us in our showroom at @imtschicago to discover all the features of the PUMA TT1300SYY. It\xe2\x80\x99s the horizontal turning center with all the bells and whistles. Don\xe2\x80\x99t miss it. Visit the link in our bio and save it to your MySpark Planner.'

b'Brand new installation of a BMO Platinum sideloader next to a 5-axis Doosan DVF 5000. Repost @bmo_automation. \xe2\x80\x9cThe robot loads and unloads products and pallet fixtures into the Doosan machine.\xe2\x80\x9d'

b'Friday the 13th? Pretty spooky. In 2020? EXTRA SPOOKY. But not to worry; you have the magical essence of Doosan on your shop floor. In fact, this could be your lucky day. Run that special piece, snap a photo of it and post it using the hashtag #PARTPRIDE and you might find a prize box on your doorstep.  Link in bio to see the winners so far.'

b'Spec of the Week: 49.6 hp. That\xe2\x80\x99s the powerful output of the optional main spindle on the PUMA SMX5100LS Multifunction Turn Mill Center. It\xe2\x80\x99s brawny enough to create 3,096ft-lb of torque.\n\nThe milling and turning capabilities of the SMX series allow for fast and precise machining of workpieces in one set-up. With a total of nine axes, the only limit is your imagination.'
b'Which I/O channel is best? There are lots to choose from, and we go over it in the latest episode of Know Your Doosan. Link in bio with the full video.'
b'This Doosan PUMA 400L is "turning" out the parts. Repost @off_omec. :OK_hand:'
b'If you want to get the most out of your Doosan machine tools, Mark\xe2\x80\x99s your man. If you\xe2\x80\x99re casting the next Hollywood blockbuster, not so much.'

b'Chip of the Week: The Advantages Of Live Tooling. \n"Used my lathe as a mill to machine a simple step on a aluminum part." The secret to this procedure is having live tooling capability. Repost @cnctobi.'

b"Machining aerospace parts often means titanium is in the work holder. In this video, the @titansofcnc show how it's done by finishing a titanium part on the PUMA SMX 3100ST. Great shots of lathe work being done with the top spindle. Link in bio to full video."
b'There\xe2\x80\x99s no Trick to machining perfect parts. Treat yourself to a Doosan machine tool and see how sweet life can really be. Zero calories and no sugar added.:ghost::candy:'

b'The folks at PGI Steel build big, heavy-duty, rigid equipment every day, and they know what to look for. When they installed the Doosan DBM 2540, they saw a reflection of their own quality standards (and they painted the floor to match the machine). Link in bio.'

b'The DBM 2540 will make a meal out of any heavy-hogging application. And with some of the biggest specs in its class, you\xe2\x80\x99d best believe that it always shows up hungry. Link in bio for video. :flexed_biceps:'

b'Spec of the Week: 8 tons. Parts weighing up to 8 tons can be loaded and machined accurately in the new PUMA VTR1012FC ram-type vertical turning center. This is due to the machine\xe2\x80\x99s high stiffness characteristics which allow extreme stability even during heavy cutting.\n\nThe VTR Series has a massive wide column parked on top of the one-piece bed, which is what allows it to have some of the largest VTC specs in the industry.'

b'The A-axis nodding head spindle and direct-drive B-axis rotary table allow the DHF 8000ST to handle a complete range of machining and turning processes from roughing to finishing in a single setup. Link in bio.'

b'Miami-based CNC shop @machiningwithmeaning just launched this year. It operates on a part-time basis to honor the memory of a great friend, and to give back to a charity that was near and dear to him. Link in bio.'

b'We\xe2\x80\x99ve been working with @fanucamerica controls since the late 1970\xe2\x80\x99s, and have learned how to optimize their systems to get the most for each application. Here, an operator is hard at work tending to a NHP 5000 horizontal machining center.'
b'September #PartPride winner alert! Shouts to @rennenbmx, who uses the Lynx 2100LSY to produce these killer mini BMX cranks. Details in bio link. \n\n#DoosanShop #MachineGreatness'

b"Don\xe2\x80\x99t mind us, we\xe2\x80\x99re just over here getting hyped for today's live demo of the NHP 5000 in our @imtschicago showroom. At 11 AM CST, we\xe2\x80\x99ll be showcasing one of our favorite horizontal machining centers and talking automated pallet systems. Link in bio to join."
b'Aluminum parts for racing bikes.:motorcycle_selector: Repost @fastecracing "Fantastic workmanship in these parts."'

b'Not much gets us hyped more than a quality Inconel shot. Drilling 1.5\xe2\x80\x9d diameter hole thru 11.25\xe2\x80\x9d of 2.5\xe2\x80\x9d diameter solid Inconel601 bars. By the way, we were trying to guess what the purple line is. Our best guess is a lightsaber.'

b'If you\xe2\x80\x99ve got an interest in HMCs, then we\xe2\x80\x99ve got a treat for you. On October 13th, we\xe2\x80\x99re doing our first #IMTSSpark demo of the NHP 5000 in our showroom at @imtschicago. Join us to see an impressive machine do its thing, along with how easy it is to set up with our Linear Pallet System. Visit the link in our bio and save it to your MySpark Planner.'

b'Get off of Instagram and run a full backup of your Doosan machine right now. We\xe2\x80\x99ll wait. Oh, and if you\xe2\x80\x99re not sure how, Episode 8 of Know Your Doosan has you covered. Link in bio with the full video.'
b'This little beauty takes the prize. :trophy: Repost @xenium_cnc: \xe2\x80\x9cCool part.\xe2\x80\x9d'

b'Knock, knock who\xe2\x80\x99s there? All the great content in our @imtschicago Spark Showroom. Browse our featured video content, connect with us or register for upcoming live demos. And if you add us to your MySpark Planner you won\xe2\x80\x99t miss a moment of #MachineGreatness. \nAdded bonus? No more fake knock knock jokes. Link in bio.'

b'Chip of the week: If you\xe2\x80\x99re removing massive amounts of metal, you\xe2\x80\x99d better order yourself a Doosan. Take a gander at this excavation job done on an NHP 4000. Repost @huntermanufacturingservices.'

b'The heavy-duty bridge mills in our new DBM series are the big brothers to our popular BM model. The 50 taper, 8,000 r/min RAM type spindle with a built-in motor outputs 50 horses and 745 ft-lb of torque at just 350 r/min for your all your heavy hogging applications. Great for oversized die molds, too. Three models to choose from. Link in bio for more info.'
b'Nice form. :flexed_biceps: Repost @ubmathis: "Do you even lift, bro?"'

b'Spec of the Week: 1,212. The number of ft-lbs of torque generated by the main spindle of the Doosan PUMA SMX5100L multifunction mill turn center. Whatever you plan to make, this machine is up for it.'

b"We've got ourselves an August #PartPride winner, people. A big ol' prize box is headed to Seth, aka @somemachinist, who used the PUMA 2600SYII to produce this tight-tolerance aerospace part. Link in bio with details. :clapping_hands_light_skin_tone:"

b'The HFP 1540, our 5-axis profiler, has an outrageously fast HSK taper 30,000 RPM spindle, a massive table for the largest aerospace components you produce and a 5-axis universal head that gives you machining angles you don\xe2\x80\x99t get with typical horizontals. \nEnough words. Link in bio for the full video.'

b'That\xe2\x80\x99s a pretty bold statement, but Jerry says that quality construction, outstanding reliability, availability, customer support and excellent price points are key elements in Doosan\xe2\x80\x99s favor. Read the full story. Link in bio.'

b"Can't find the right tool? Make one by using your Doosan machine. Repost @cnctobi: \xe2\x80\x9cLately I had a lot of parts out of PA6 XT to mill and had problems with quick wear on normal carbide inserts. Then I wanted to try PCD inserts but I only had CCMT 0602 so I made a face mill for them.\xe2\x80\x9d"

b'Last but not least, @titansofcnc is showing you how to tool up for big cuts. The final day of BOOMBASTIC SHOW features the beastly Mynx 6500/50 AND your last chance to get that TITANS discount. Links in bio.'
b"Chip of the week: IMTS 2018.\n\nIt's been quite a year, huh? Can't wait until we're all back in Chicago again."

b"Get hyped, because it's Day 4 of :collision: BOOMBASTIC SHOW :collision: Today @titansofcnc has the PUMA 2600SYII, a lathe that dominates the complex materials. Link in bio to the live tooling demo."

b'Day 3 of the @titansofcnc BOOMBASTIC SHOW is all about the powerful NHM 6300 horizontal machining center. Check out the aerospace demo and get more info on the TITAN Training Package. Links in bio.'

b'The @titansofcnc BOOMBASTIC SHOW is covering some big stuff in Day 2: a deep dive into the 5-axis DVF 6500 and a first look at the TITAN Training Package. Link in bio to the Day 2 stream. \n\n#MachineGreatness #DoosanShop'

b"Ohhhhh man. @titansofcnc just wrapped Episode 1 of BOOMBASTIC SHOW, and it's huge. Our 9-axis mill/turn, the PUMA SMX 3100ST, was the focal point. Link in bio that takes you straight to the stream. Stay tuned to the TITANS Facebook page this week, because there's more coming."
b'At Doosan, we have no tolerance for loose tolerances. Repost @alek.symarip.'

b'In the past 20 years, @joegibbsracing has collected five @nascar Cup Series Championships and three Daytona 500 victories. In the past 20 years, the team has depended on Doosan machine tools. Coincidence? Nah. Link in bio.'

b"All next week, @titansofcnc is hosting THE BOOMBASTIC SHOW. Tune into their Facebook feed and you'll see some crazy CNC machining (and limited-time Doosan machine discounts). \n\n#MachineGreatness #DoosanShop"

b'You know what we appreciate even more than our complete line of CNC machines? The wonderful men and women who operate them. Today we take time to thank them for their continuing efforts. It is this combination of technology and skill that keeps U.S. manufacturing strong.'

b'Why settle for less? This customer is taking delivery of a DNM 750II, the best-in-class vertical machining center that comes fully equipped with the most standard features built-in. Repost @techmach_arkansas.'
b'Episode 7 of Know Your Doosan is all about getting the pallet changer back up and running after a power loss. Crash course starts now. Link in bio to the full video.'
b'Grow your #CNC production business with #hmc, #vmc and #turningmachines from Doosan and @techmach_arkansas. Here\xe2\x80\x99s how AMET does it. Link in bio for the full story.'
b'The Doosan Tool Load Monitor is a great feature for lights out machining and high production work. Get the most out of it by watching this video from @titansofcnc. Link to full video in bio.'

b"Whether it is aluminum, titanium or stainless steel, when you think of turning parts, most people think of metal. The fact is, orders come through the door for all types of materials today. For example, acrylic and other plastics are used in a variety of industries due to their non-conductive properties. The good news is, whatever you're machining, we can hook you up with the perfect CNC equipment for your needs. Repost @cnctobi."

b'Spec of the Week: 2.9. All the seconds you need for the APC on the Doosan VC 3600 high productivity machining center to switch out pallets. It\xe2\x80\x99s standard and that\xe2\x80\x99s added-value. You\xe2\x80\x99re welcome.'
b'Our customers love the Lynx 2100LSYB turning center. They just wanted us to make it a little bit bigger. So, we did. Meet the new Lynx 2600SY. Link in bio.'
b'A compact and automation-ready 5-axis powerhouse. You can try to find more performance per dollar than what the DVF 6500 gives you, but we\xe2\x80\x99ll save you some time: you won\xe2\x80\x99t.'

b"Stainless steel is one of the more difficult materials to machine. But when a seasoned operator and the right machine tool come together, the results can be outstanding. Put a Doosan on your shop floor and you're half way there. Repost @wolf.river.machine.llc."
b'@titansofcnc gave some titanium to their very hungry Mynx, then they sat back and enjoyed the MRR. Now you can too. Link to full video in bio.'

b'Spec of the Week: 6,600. The table on Doosan\xe2\x80\x99s HFP 1540 horizontal 5-axis profiler can hold this weight in pounds. Capacity like that will instantly elevate your shop\xe2\x80\x99s aerospace work to world-class heights.'

b"Doosan's lineup of 5-axis machines has enough variety to provide a perfect match between equipment and application. Just look at the awesome surface finish on this part machined on a DVF 5000. Repost @xenium_cnc."

b'Chip of the Week: A little downtime for routine maintenance ensures a continuous high level of performance. \xe2\x80\x9cOur 5-axis is getting some well-earned TLC today.\xe2\x80\x9d Repost @fastecracing.'

b'In the past 20 years, @joegibbsracing has collected five NASCAR Cup Series Championships and three Daytona 500 victories. In the past 20 years, the team has depended on Doosan machine tools. Coincidence? Nah. Link in bio.'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cPierson Workholding hits the coolant routine maintenance like an MLB slugger and it makes ALL the difference. Better parts, longer lasting machines, etc., etc.\xe2\x80\x9d Repost @factory400.'

b'There were a ton of excellent Part Pride entries this month, but it was @horsepowerinc who came out on top with this gorgeous motorcycle throttle body and intake replacement, made with the DNM 400 HS and the DMV 4020LS. Congrats to this shop. Your prize box is in the mail! \n\nLearn more about the part in our bio link.'

b'Fun fact about our horizontal milling machines: they love large tools. Plus, safely getting those tools in and out of the work zone is easier than you might think. Episode 6 of Know Your Doosan is here. Link in bio.'

b'Forward Technologies, Inc out of Cincinnati, Ohio runs three shifts per day, and churns out parts for a variety of industries. They needed machines that could keep up with demand and offer versatility, then they got their first Doosan. It was love at first run.\n\nLink in bio for the full story.'

b'Knight Design wanted to expand capacity quickly with state-of-the-art machine tools. They were looking for quality combined with excellent price points. Who\xe2\x80\x99d they call? Doosan, of course.'

b'Chip of the Week: Monster parts demand monster machine tools. Try the PUMA 3100XLY on for size. Chuck size ranges from 12\xe2\x80\x9d to 15\xe2\x80\x9d, and the ultra rigid construction ensures accuracy you can rely on. \n#MachineGreatness #DoosanShop'
b'The NHP 5000 is a difference-making machine all on its own. But when paired with a Rotary Pallet System? Hoooooo, buddy. #MachineGreatness'

b'Precious cargo coming in.This DBM 2540 will machine large parts and high precision dies and molds in no time. I wouldn\'t stand there if I were you. Just saying. Repost @ubmathis. "Look. It\'s a bird. It\'s a plane..."'

b'Have you made a part on a Doosan machine that deserves to be applauded? Take a photo and post it using the hashtag #PARTPRIDE. Get some props and win a prize. A new winner every month. \n\nDetails and how to enter in bio.'

b'BREAKING: The Part Pride kits have landed, and they\xe2\x80\x99re the real deal. Here\xe2\x80\x99s @laurenswijnschenk with an unboxing. Want one of your own? Just show us what your Doosan made, use the #PartPride hashtag and you\xe2\x80\x99re entered to win.'

b'With its built-in size and strength, the new PUMA SMX5100L/LS is ideal for aerospace applications such as components for landing gears as well as housings for large shafts like those found in the agriculture or oil field industries. Link in bio for more details.'

b'Doosan distributor MTS was honored to be part of the ribbon cutting for Metal Arts\xe2\x80\x99 Wichita facility. A big highlight was their newly purchased NHP 4000 with 12 station LPS and 275 ATC. Time to fire it up and crank out the parts. Repost @machinetoolspecialties.'

b"We\xe2\x80\x99ve got a June #PartPride winner: shouts to @daveringer, who used a Daewoo DMV 4020D for this camshaft vibration damper part. Want to share what your Doosan made? b'Chip of the Week: Schedule time for routine maintenance. It will keep your Doosan #machinetool operating at full capacity day and night.'
b'Hesitant to move from Japanese machine tools? Read how True Precision Machining took the plunge with help from @ellisontech and never looked back. Link in bio.'

b'Why does SCHUNK, a worldwide leader in workholding and tool holding products, use Doosan machines in their facilities? They are considered to be the perfect value machines for their processes \xe2\x80\x93 heavy duty, fast and reliable.'
b'Here\xe2\x80\x99s a guy who really keeps his head in the game. He and his buddies know that for the really big turning jobs, the call goes to the PUMA VT1100. Repost @tecnocozzi.'

b'Spec of the Week: 12. That\xe2\x80\x99s the number of tool stations available in the #ATC magazine that comes standard with the PUMA V8300. The tools remain safely out of the way when not in use, providing superior tool management and much easier maintenance.'

b'We\xe2\x80\x99re excited to reveal that we are the exclusive premier machine tool builder partner for @titansofcnc. Together, we\xe2\x80\x99ll train up the next generation of machinists and equip them to do world-changing things. #MachineGreatness'
